content.problemStatement:
The **range with start and end** in Java is implemented using a **for loop**, allowing iteration over a specific sequence of numbers. It defines a **starting value** and an **ending condition**, ensuring controlled execution within a fixed range.

 **Syntax:**
```java
for (int i = start; i <= end; i++) {
    // Code to execute in each iteration
}
```
---

**Example:**

```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int start = 2; // Starting value of the range
        int end = 5; // Ending value of the range

        // Loop from start to end, printing each number
        for (int i = start; i <= end; i++) {
            System.out.println(i); // Print the current value of i
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**
```default
2
3
4
5
```

